The ANC is celebrating its 111 anniversary in Bloemfontein. #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - The South African Communist Party's Solly Mapaila has challenged the ANC to put an end to ongoing power cuts. Mapaila made this call at the party's 111th birthday celebration in Mangaung, in the Free State. READ:Â Expert says to expect more power cuts At the same event, ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa said that ending blackouts and solving the energy crisis is one of the party's top priorities. Ramaphosa has also conceded that load-shedding is harming the country's economic growth. The country is currently on Stage 4 power cuts.